# i18n Translation Guidelines

## Core Rule
- Treat `nextjs/src/messages/en.json` as the source of truth.
- Keep every locale file in `nextjs/src/messages/*.json` aligned to the same namespaces and key paths as `en.json` (currently: `es`, `de`, `fr`, `it`, `ja`, `ko`, `pl`, `pt`).
- Do not change locale routing defaults unless explicitly requested.

## Required Behavior
- You should do these translations through your own weights and model rather than using a translation API. You only need to translate new keys, do not retranslate the whole file or other keys that we are not adding.
- When adding or editing text, update English first, then mirror the same key path in all other locale files.
- Preserve ICU placeholders exactly (same names and braces), e.g. `{amount}`, `{code}`, `{rewardName}`.
- Keep key structure stable; do not rename/move keys unless asked.
- For metadata strings, keep parity across all locale files and preserve matching key names.
- Prefer concise copy that is close in visual length to English when possible, especially for nav items, buttons, hero headings, and animated text.
- If a direct translation is much longer, rewrite to a natural but shorter equivalent rather than literal wording.
- Never introduce manual line breaks (`\n`) or formatting hacks to force wrapping.
- Before finishing, verify the edited key path exists in every locale file.

## Safe Edit Examples

### Add new key from English base
```json
// en.json
"RewardMetadata": { "newBanner": "Redeem faster this week" }
// every other locale file (same key path)
"RewardMetadata": { "newBanner": "<localized string>" }
```

### Update existing key in both locales
```json
// en.json
"Common": { "loading": "Loading rewards..." }
// every other locale file (same key path)
"Common": { "loading": "<localized string>" }
```

### Preserve placeholders exactly
```json
// en.json
"cashbackLine": "Get up to {amount} back"
// every other locale file (same placeholder token)
"cashbackLine": "<localized text with {amount}>"
```

### Metadata parity
```json
// keep same paths in every locale file
"TermsOfServiceMetadata": { "title": "...", "description": "..." }
```
